  "texts": [
    "The emergence of code agent benchmarks, such as SWT-Bench, provides support for evaluating these end-to-end workflows [97].",
    "The ultimate goal is to achieve end-to-end, truly human-free autonomous testing.",
    "Recent research has begun to put this vision into practice by building multi-agent collaborative frameworks to achieve end-to-end test generation.",
    "For example, CANDOR decomposes tasks such as test planning, code generation, verification, and assertion correction to agents with different roles, and effectively reduces hallucination issues in assertion generation through a consensus mechanism involving a 'panel of experts' discussion [147].",
    "Other multi-agent frameworks demonstrate stronger adaptive repair capabilities, where agents, through iterative feedback, can not only modify test cases but also dynamically adjust the program under test itself to ensure consistency between the code and the requirement specifications [82]."
  ],
